Key Match Events: USA won the Super Over against Pakistan.
Saurabh Netravalkar took 2 for 18 in regular play and bowled effectively in the Super Over.
Nosthush Kenjige took 3 for 30, including key wickets of Shadab Khan and Azam Khan.
Mohammad Amir bowled three wides in the Super Over, contributing to Pakistan's loss.
Jones hit a six off the penultimate ball to tie the game, and Nitish Kumar hit a four off the last ball to force the Super Over.
Post-Match Reflections: Babar Azam admitted Pakistan were 'not up to the mark' in bowling.
The USA team was jubilant after taking down a major opponent.
Miscellaneous Highlights: USA's victory was described as a significant achievement, marking their first major act of giant-killing on the global stage.
